                                 [bmelg.gif]

   Included in Natural Selection November 5, 2001. Natural Selection is a
   gateway to quality evaluated Internet resources in the natural world,
   coordinated by The Natural History Museum, London. Natural Selection is
   part of BIOME, an integrated collection of Internet gateways covering
   the health and life sciences.
     Featured site for Summer 2001, by the Arctic Circle, August 1, 2001.
   [websel.gif] Current Web Contents, January 10, 2001
